  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-07-21",
    "date": "2020-08-27T14:46:39Z",
    "text": "This bill makes permanent the reduction in the adjusted gross income (AGI) threshold that must be exceeded before a taxpayer may claim a deduction amount for medical expenses. The reduction is from 10% to 7.5% of AGI and 5% in any taxable year beginnning in 2020 or 2021."
